d, The Walnut Mansion may be read as an allegory of the tragedy of Yugoslavia’s tormented twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCroatian fiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aDickey, Stephen M ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDickey, Stephen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPavetic-Dickey, Janja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030017927940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018481540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300184815423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300184815/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY